msgstr "%s关闭。"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Chinese power armor (active)', 'str_pl':
#. 'Chinese power armors (active)'}
#: .\gb_armor.json
msgid ""
"Developed after the groundbreaking creation of power armor by the United "
"States, the Type-13 combat exoskeleton was China's attempt at making an "
"equivalent to the United States. Development of these suits of protection "
"were significantly rushed though, and are often inferior to their American "
"counterparts, if a bit lighter to wear.  It is currently turned on, activate"
" it to turn it off."
msgstr ""
"在美国开创性地研发出动力装甲后，中国为打造与之匹敌的装备而开发了13型战斗外骨骼。然而这些防护服的研发进程极为仓促，虽穿戴稍轻便，但性能通常逊于美国同类产品。当前为开启状态，需手动激活以关闭。"

#: .\gb_armor.json
msgid "Chinese power armor helmet"
msgid_plural "Chinese power armor helmets"
msgstr[0] "中国动力装甲头盔"

#. ~ Use action msg for {'str': 'Chinese power armor helmet'}.
#. ~ Use action msg for {'str': 'Chi Industries combat headset'}.
#. ~ Use action msg for {'str': 'XEDRA excursion suit helmet'}.
#: .\gb_armor.json
msgid "The %s seals shut and beeps once."
msgstr "%s密封关闭并发出一次提示音。"

#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Chinese power armor helmet'}
#. ~ Description for {'str': 'Chinese power armor helmet (active)', 'str_pl':
#. 'Chinese power armor helmets (active)'}
#: .\gb_armor.json
msgid ""
"A fully enclosed combat helmet for hazardous environments and combat zones "
"the Chinese military expected to find itself in, this was designed to fit "
"with a powered exoskeleton, using cameras to expand visual range.  In "
"practice, the cameras were unreliable and easily fouled.  The environmental "
"controls function best with direct-skin contact."
msgstr ""
"这是为中国军队预期将进入的危险环境与战区设计的全封闭式战斗头盔，可与动力外骨骼配套使用，通过摄像头扩展视野范围。实际上，这些摄像头可靠性差且易受干扰。环境控制系统在直接接触皮肤时效果最佳。"

#: .\gb_armor.json
msgid "Chinese power armor helmet (active)"
msgid_plural "Chinese power armor helmets (active)"
msgstr[0] "中国动力装甲头盔（已激活）"

